          <p><em>For those flying to Boston</em>: the quickest way into the city from Logan Airport (besides taxi) is to take the <a href="https://www.massport.com/logan-airport/to-and-from-logan/logan-express/back-bay/">Logan Express to Back Bay</a>. Otherwise, you can take the Silver Line for free to South Station, and from there take the Red Line almost anywhere via transfer options to all lines.</p>
          <em>Accomodation:</em> Boston is not known to be inexpensive, and the hotels in the immediate vicinity of our ceremony are no exception. That being said, you'll find reasonably-priced accomodation throughout the greater metro area. Several recommended hotels include <a href="https://gc.synxis.com/rez.aspx?chain=5433&hotel=56668&_ga=1.73938906.951254481.1483069607">Revere Boston</a>, <a href="https://bookings.ihotelier.com/Newbury-Guest-House/select_rooms.jsp;jsessionid=06C56AA349907051AFE7902C94F21F02?hotelId=3803&urlredirect=yes&y=4&x=19">Newbury Guest House</a>, <a href="http://www.theamoryhouse.com/">Amory Guest House</a>, and <a href="http://www.starwoodhotels.com/whotels/property/overview/index.html?propertyID=1787&language=en_US">The W Boston</a> (our personal favorite). There are also countless options available on <a href="https://www.airbnb.com/s/Boston--MA--United-States?adults=4&checkin=10%2F20%2F2017&checkout=10%2F22%2F2017&children=0&guests=4&infants=0&room_types%5B%5D=Entire%20home%2Fapt&room_types%5B%5D=Private%20room&source=bb&ss_id=h69w4l7z&ss_preload=false&allow_override%5B%5D=&page=1&s_tag=cH1GGx0F">Airbnb</a>, many of them considerably more affordable. 
